==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topek
<hw>To"pek</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Eskimo
<ets>tupek</ets>.]</ety> <def>An Eskimo house made of material other
than snow, esp. one having walls of turf, driftwood, rock, or skin, and
a roof of skins of the walrus or seal. In Alaska it is often partially
underground and covered with timber and turf. Topeks are also used by
Indians of the lower <geog>Yukon</geog> region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toper</ent>⟦br⟧
